          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone h='22321' id='8' name='Attrition by Department' w='48243' x='4539' y='19770' />
        <zone h='21747' id='12' name='Attrition by Age Group' w='41801' x='55344' y='19515' />
        <zone h='23342' id='13' name='Attrition by Job Satisfaction' w='45242' x='6662' y='45663' />
        <zone h='22321' id='14' name='Attrition by Overtime' w='40117' x='55417' y='45281' />
        <zone h='8355' id='17' name='Total Employees' w='15447' x='15666' y='8801' />
        <zone h='8355' id='18' name='Employees Left' w='15447' x='42679' y='6441' />
        <zone h='8355' id='19' name='Attrition Rate' w='16398' x='70059' y='8291' />
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='30038' id='20' type-v2='text' w='97365' x='1318' y='70153'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='20'>Key Insights</run>
            <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>• Out of 1,470 employees, 237 have left from the organization resulting in an attrition rate of 16.12%.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>• The highest rate of turnover amongst employees exists within the Research and Development division while Human Resources division has the lowest number of turnover employees.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>• Most of the attritions have come out to be people aged between 20 and 39 indicating that the attrition rate is higher amongst young employees.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>• Overtime workers tend to leave the organization more frequently as compared to other non-overtime workers, indicating a probable effect of work pressure on employee turnover.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>• Attrition rates exist amongst all levels of job satisfaction among the employees indicating that multiple reasons affect the attrition rate among employees.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
